2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper focuses on the subjective quality of images and videos, which is an important aspect of human-computer interaction. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with the rendering of images and videos, which is a key area of research in computer graphics. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of image quality on human perception, which is a key area of research in multimedia. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses the use of analytical models to reduce the transmission data size without subjective quality loss, which is relevant to information retrieval.
